  "interpretation": "Intertemporal elasticity of substitution for nondurable consumption in a representative U.S. household annual macro-calibration setting, defined as the percent change in the growth rate of nondurable consumption from a 1 percent change in the intertemporal price of consumption, treated as a consumption-growth response parameter distinct from risk aversion.",
